---
const features = [
  { icon: "🔌", title: "Hook-First Architecture", body: "The turn pipeline <em>is</em> hooks. Builtins are ordinary plugins — no magic, no special cases. Override <code>build_prompt</code>, <code>run_model_stream</code>, or <code>render_outbound</code> simply by registering your own." },
  { icon: "📼", title: "Tape-Based Context", body: "History is append-only facts. Context is assembled on demand — not accumulated, not compressed into lossy summaries. Your working set is always current." },
  { icon: "📡", title: "Channel-Agnostic Pipeline", body: "CLI and Telegram share the same <code>process_inbound()</code> path. Hooks don't know which channel they're in. Adding a new channel is just implementing one interface." },
  { icon: "📄", title: "Skills as Documents", body: "Skills are <code>SKILL.md</code> files with validated frontmatter, not code modules with magic registration. Ship them in packages. Override them per-workspace or per-user." },
  { icon: "🧩", title: "~200-Line Core", body: "The core is intentionally small. Builtins are default plugins you can replace. No privileged internal path. Every default is an example of how to write a plugin." },
  { icon: "🤝", title: "Socialized Evaluation", body: "Humans and agents share the same operator model. Execution is visible, handoff is safe, and continuation is predictable — even when multiple people and agents are working in the same context." },
  { icon: "🔧", title: "Plugin Ecosystem", body: "External plugins load via Python entry-points. Later-registered plugins run first. Any builtin behavior can be overridden — or wrapped — without forking the core." },
  { icon: "🌐", title: "Multi-Channel Gateway", body: "<code>bub gateway</code> starts a channel listener for Telegram and any adapter you add. The same skills, the same context, the same hooks — across every surface." },
];
---

<section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 md:px-12 pb-20 md:pb-28">
  <div class="text-center mb-10">
    <p class="text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.12em] uppercase text-[#4f7eff] mb-2">Why Bub</p>
    <h2 class="text-[clamp(1.5rem,3vw,2.2rem)] font-extrabold tracking-tight mb-3">Built for real teams, not demos</h2>
    <p class="text-[#888b99] max-w-xl mx-auto text-sm md:text-base">
      Bub grew up in multi-person group chats where single-user assumptions
      break immediately. These constraints shaped everything.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 xl:grid-cols-4 gap-5">
    {features.map(({ icon, title, body }) => (
      <div class="bg-[#1a1d2e] border border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.08)] rounded-[10px] p-6 transition-all duration-200 hover:border-[rgba(79,126,255,0.35)] hover:-translate-y-0.5">
        <div class="text-2xl mb-3">{icon}</div>
        <h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-1.5 text-[#e8eaf6]">{title}</h3>
        <p class="text-[0.875rem] text-[#888b99] leading-[1.55]" set:html={body} />
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>
</section>
